 [1mUse higher precision when calculating breakpoint-max values[22m

   Bootstrap is currently using `0.1` as the value for calculating
   `breakpoint-max`. This causes an issue when using the `hidden-*-down`
   classes.    For example (assume font-size: 16px):  md: 48em, // 48 *
   16 = 768px  breakpoint-max(md, (xs: 0, sm: 34rem, md: 48rem)): 47.9 //
   47.9 * 16 = 766.4    This leaves a ~2px window where elements with
   `hidden-md-down` will show up unexpectedly.    I'm proposing changing
   the precision value to 0.00001. I'm not sure that 5 places are needed
   (too much?), but since that seems to be the default precision for
   SASS, I went with that.
